		$strMainCopy	=	"<h1>Paperwork required for your civil wedding in Greece or Cyprus</h1>
		<p>The following is intended as a guide to the documents that you will need in order to have a civil wedding in Greece or Cyprus.  If you wish to have a Catholic, Anglican or Orthodox wedding, please <a href='?PTID=9' target='_self' title='contact us'>contact us</a> for more information. It may vary slightly from island to island and this information is subject to change, so please check with the relevant authorities beforehand.</p> 
		<p>If you use our services, we will provide you with up to date information, costs and full assistance with the paperwork.  We can even do most of the paperwork for you, for a small fee, to save you queuing at the embassy!  <a href='?PTID=9' target='_self' title='Contact us'>Contact us</a> for more information on our Documentation Service.</p>
		<p>Some islands require you to be on the island for a certain number of days before your wedding.  We can advise you which ones these are and which are more flexible. In general, you will need to send the following documentation over to Greece or Cyprus.  It should be sent a minimum of 2 months before your wedding:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Birth certificate (for each party).  These must be full birth certificates showing parents' names</li>
